1/* LzmaDec.c -- LZMA Decoder
2 2009-09-20 : Igor Pavlov : Public domain */
3
4#include "LzmaDec.h"
5
6#include <string.h>
7
8#define kNumTopBits 24
9#define kTopValue ((UInt32)1 << kNumTopBits)
10
11#define kNumBitModelTotalBits 11
12#define kBitModelTotal (1 << kNumBitModelTotalBits)
13#define kNumMoveBits 5
14
15#define RC_INIT_SIZE 5
16
17#define NORMALIZE if (range < kTopValue) { range <<= 8; code = (code << 8) | (*buf++); }
18
19#define IF_BIT_0(p) ttt = *(p); NORMALIZE; bound = (range >> kNumBitModelTotalBits) * ttt; if (code < bound)
20#define UPDATE_0(p) range = bound; *(p) = (CLzmaProb)(ttt + ((kBitModelTotal - ttt) >> kNumMoveBits));
21#define UPDATE_1(p) range -= bound; code -= bound; *(p) = (CLzmaProb)(ttt - (ttt >> kNumMoveBits));
22#define GET_BIT2(p, i, A0, A1) IF_BIT_0(p) \
23 { UPDATE_0(p); i = (i + i); A0; } else \
24 { UPDATE_1(p); i = (i + i) + 1; A1; }
25#define GET_BIT(p, i) GET_BIT2(p, i, ; , ;)
26
27#define TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i) { GET_BIT((probs + i), i); }
28#define TREE_DECODE(probs, limit, i) \
29 { i = 1; do { TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); } while (i < limit); i -= limit; }
30
31/* #define _LZMA_SIZE_OPT */
32
33#ifdef _LZMA_SIZE_OPT
34#define TREE_6_DECODE(probs, i) TREE_DECODE(probs, (1 << 6), i)
35#else
36#define TREE_6_DECODE(probs, i) \
37 { i = 1; \
38 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
39 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
40 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
41 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
42 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
43 TREE_GET_BIT(probs, i); \
44 i -= 0x40; }
45#endif
46
47#define NORMALIZE_CHECK if (range < kTopValue) { if (buf >= bufLimit) return DUMMY_ERROR; range <<= 8; code = (code << 8) | (*buf++); }
48
49#define IF_BIT_0_CHECK(p) ttt = *(p); NORMALIZE_CHECK; bound = (range >> kNumBitModelTotalBits) * ttt; if (code < bound)
50#define UPDATE_0_CHECK range = bound;
51#define UPDATE_1_CHECK range -= bound; code -= bound;
52#define GET_BIT2_CHECK(p, i, A0, A1) IF_BIT_0_CHECK(p) \
53 { UPDATE_0_CHECK; i = (i + i); A0; } else \
54 { UPDATE_1_CHECK; i = (i + i) + 1; A1; }
55#define GET_BIT_CHECK(p, i) GET_BIT2_CHECK(p, i, ; , ;)
56#define TREE_DECODE_CHECK(probs, limit, i) \
57 { i = 1; do { GET_BIT_CHECK(probs + i, i) } while (i < limit); i -= limit; }
58
59#define kNumPosBitsMax 4
60#define kNumPosStatesMax (1 << kNumPosBitsMax)
61
62#define kLenNumLowBits 3
63#define kLenNumLowSymbols (1 << kLenNumLowBits)
64#define kLenNumMidBits 3
65#define kLenNumMidSymbols (1 << kLenNumMidBits)
66#define kLenNumHighBits 8
67#define kLenNumHighSymbols (1 << kLenNumHighBits)
68
69#define LenChoice 0
70#define LenChoice2 (LenChoice + 1)
71#define LenLow (LenChoice2 + 1)
72#define LenMid (LenLow + (kNumPosStatesMax << kLenNumLowBits))
73#define LenHigh (LenMid + (kNumPosStatesMax << kLenNumMidBits))
74#define kNumLenProbs (LenHigh + kLenNumHighSymbols)
75
76#define kNumStates 12
77#define kNumLitStates 7
78
79#define kStartPosModelIndex 4
80#define kEndPosModelIndex 14
81#define kNumFullDistances (1 << (kEndPosModelIndex >> 1))
82
83#define kNumPosSlotBits 6
84#define kNumLenToPosStates 4
85
86#define kNumAlignBits 4
87#define kAlignTableSize (1 << kNumAlignBits)
88
89#define kMatchMinLen 2
90#define kMatchSpecLenStart (kMatchMinLen + kLenNumLowSymbols + kLenNumMidSymbols + kLenNumHighSymbols)
91
92#define IsMatch 0
93#define IsRep (IsMatch + (kNumStates << kNumPosBitsMax))
94#define IsRepG0 (IsRep + kNumStates)
95#define IsRepG1 (IsRepG0 + kNumStates)
96#define IsRepG2 (IsRepG1 + kNumStates)
97#define IsRep0Long (IsRepG2 + kNumStates)
98#define PosSlot (IsRep0Long + (kNumStates << kNumPosBitsMax))
99#define SpecPos (PosSlot + (kNumLenToPosStates << kNumPosSlotBits))
100#define Align (SpecPos + kNumFullDistances - kEndPosModelIndex)
101#define LenCoder (Align + kAlignTableSize)
102#define RepLenCoder (LenCoder + kNumLenProbs)
103#define Literal (RepLenCoder + kNumLenProbs)
104
105#define LZMA_BASE_SIZE 1846
106#define LZMA_LIT_SIZE 768
107
108#define LzmaProps_GetNumProbs(p) ((UInt32)LZMA_BASE_SIZE + (LZMA_LIT_SIZE << ((p)->lc + (p)->lp)))
109
110#if Literal != LZMA_BASE_SIZE
111StopCompilingDueBUG
112#endif
113
114#define LZMA_DIC_MIN (1 << 12)
115
116/* First LZMA-symbol is always decoded.
117 And it decodes new LZMA-symbols while (buf < bufLimit), but "buf" is without last normalization
118 Out:
119 Result:
120 SZ_OK - OK
121 SZ_ERROR_DATA - Error
122 p->remainLen:
123 < kMatchSpecLenStart : normal remain
124 = kMatchSpecLenStart : finished
125 = kMatchSpecLenStart + 1 : Flush marker
126 = kMatchSpecLenStart + 2 : State Init Marker
127 */
128
129static int MY_FAST_CALL LzmaDec_DecodeReal(CLzmaDec *p, SizeT limit, const Byte *bufLimit)
130{
131 CLzmaProb *probs = p->probs;
132
133 unsigned state = p->state;
134 UInt32 rep0 = p->reps[0], rep1 = p->reps[1], rep2 = p->reps[2], rep3 = p->reps[3];
135 unsigned pbMask = ((unsigned) 1 << (p->prop.pb)) - 1;
136 unsigned lpMask = ((unsigned) 1 << (p->prop.lp)) - 1;
137 unsigned lc = p->prop.lc;
138
139 Byte *dic = p->dic;
140 SizeT dicBufSize = p->dicBufSize;
141 SizeT dicPos = p->dicPos;
142
143 UInt32 processedPos = p->processedPos;
144 UInt32 checkDicSize = p->checkDicSize;
145 unsigned len = 0;
146
147 const Byte *buf = p->buf;
148 UInt32 range = p->range;
149 UInt32 code = p->code;
150
151 do
152 {
153 CLzmaProb *prob;
154 UInt32 bound;
155 unsigned ttt;
156 unsigned posState = processedPos & pbMask;
157
158 prob = probs + IsMatch + (state << kNumPosBitsMax) + posState;
159 IF_BIT_0(prob)
160 {
161 unsigned symbol;
162 UPDATE_0(prob);
163 prob = probs + Literal;
164 if (checkDicSize != 0 || processedPos != 0)
165 prob += (LZMA_LIT_SIZE * (((processedPos & lpMask) << lc) + (dic[(dicPos == 0 ? dicBufSize : dicPos) - 1] >> (8 - lc))));
166
167 if (state < kNumLitStates)
168 {
169 state -= (state < 4) ? state : 3;
170 symbol = 1;
171 do
172 {
173 GET_BIT(prob + symbol, symbol)
174 } while (symbol < 0x100);
175 }
176 else
177 {
178 unsigned matchByte = p->dic[(dicPos - rep0) + ((dicPos < rep0) ? dicBufSize : 0)];
179 unsigned offs = 0x100;
180 state -= (state < 10) ? 3 : 6;
181 symbol = 1;
182 do
183 {
184 unsigned bit;
185 CLzmaProb *probLit;
186 matchByte <<= 1;
187 bit = (matchByte & offs);
188 probLit = prob + offs + bit + symbol;
189 GET_BIT2(probLit, symbol, offs &= ~bit, offs &= bit)
190 } while (symbol < 0x100);
191 }
192 dic[dicPos++] = (Byte) symbol;
193 processedPos++;
194 continue;
195 }
196 else
197 {
198 UPDATE_1(prob);
199 prob = probs + IsRep + state;
200 IF_BIT_0(prob)
201 {
202 UPDATE_0(prob);
203 state += kNumStates;
204 prob = probs + LenCoder;
205 }
206 else
207 {
208 UPDATE_1(prob);
209 if (checkDicSize == 0 && processedPos == 0)
210 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
211 prob = probs + IsRepG0 + state;
212 IF_BIT_0(prob)
213 {
214 UPDATE_0(prob);
215 prob = probs + IsRep0Long + (state << kNumPosBitsMax) + posState;
216 IF_BIT_0(prob)
217 {
218 UPDATE_0(prob);
219 dic[dicPos] = dic[(dicPos - rep0) + ((dicPos < rep0) ? dicBufSize : 0)];
220 dicPos++;
221 processedPos++;
222 state = state < kNumLitStates ? 9 : 11;
223 continue;
224 }
225 UPDATE_1(prob);
226 }
227 else
228 {
229 UInt32 distance;
230 UPDATE_1(prob);
231 prob = probs + IsRepG1 + state;
232 IF_BIT_0(prob)
233 {
234 UPDATE_0(prob);
235 distance = rep1;
236 }
237 else
238 {
239 UPDATE_1(prob);
240 prob = probs + IsRepG2 + state;
241 IF_BIT_0(prob)
242 {
243 UPDATE_0(prob);
244 distance = rep2;
245 }
246 else
247 {
248 UPDATE_1(prob);
249 distance = rep3;
250 rep3 = rep2;
251 }
252 rep2 = rep1;
253 }
254 rep1 = rep0;
255 rep0 = distance;
256 }
257 state = state < kNumLitStates ? 8 : 11;
258 prob = probs + RepLenCoder;
259 }
260 {
261 unsigned limit, offset;
262 CLzmaProb *probLen = prob + LenChoice;
263 IF_BIT_0(probLen)
264 {
265 UPDATE_0(probLen);
266 probLen = prob + LenLow + (posState << kLenNumLowBits);
267 offset = 0;
268 limit = (1 << kLenNumLowBits);
269 }
270 else
271 {
272 UPDATE_1(probLen);
273 probLen = prob + LenChoice2;
274 IF_BIT_0(probLen)
275 {
276 UPDATE_0(probLen);
277 probLen = prob + LenMid + (posState << kLenNumMidBits);
278 offset = kLenNumLowSymbols;
279 limit = (1 << kLenNumMidBits);
280 }
281 else
282 {
283 UPDATE_1(probLen);
284 probLen = prob + LenHigh;
285 offset = kLenNumLowSymbols + kLenNumMidSymbols;
286 limit = (1 << kLenNumHighBits);
287 }
288 }
289 TREE_DECODE(probLen, limit, len);
290 len += offset;
291 }
292
293 if (state >= kNumStates)
294 {
295 UInt32 distance;
296 prob = probs + PosSlot + ((len < kNumLenToPosStates ? len : kNumLenToPosStates - 1) << kNumPosSlotBits);
297 TREE_6_DECODE(prob, distance);
298 if (distance >= kStartPosModelIndex)
299 {
300 unsigned posSlot = (unsigned) distance;
301 int numDirectBits = (int) (((distance >> 1) - 1));
302 distance = (2 | (distance & 1));
303 if (posSlot < kEndPosModelIndex)
304 {
305 distance <<= numDirectBits;
306 prob = probs + SpecPos + distance - posSlot - 1;
307 {
308 UInt32 mask = 1;
309 unsigned i = 1;
310 do
311 {
312 GET_BIT2(prob + i, i,; , distance |= mask);
313 mask <<= 1;
314 } while (--numDirectBits != 0);
315 }
316 }
317 else
318 {
319 numDirectBits -= kNumAlignBits;
320 do
321 {
322 NORMALIZE
323 range >>= 1;
324
325 {
326 UInt32 t;
327 code -= range;
328 t = (0 - ((UInt32) code >> 31)); /* (UInt32)((Int32)code >> 31) */
329 distance = (distance << 1) + (t + 1);
330 code += range & t;
331 }
332 /*
333 distance <<= 1;
334 if (code >= range)
335 {
336 code -= range;
337 distance |= 1;
338 }
339 */
340 } while (--numDirectBits != 0);
341 prob = probs + Align;
342 distance <<= kNumAlignBits;
343 {
344 unsigned i = 1;
345 GET_BIT2(prob + i, i,; , distance |= 1);
346 GET_BIT2(prob + i, i,; , distance |= 2);
347 GET_BIT2(prob + i, i,; , distance |= 4);
348 GET_BIT2(prob + i, i,; , distance |= 8);
349 }
350 if (distance == (UInt32) 0xFFFFFFFF)
351 {
352 len += kMatchSpecLenStart;
353 state -= kNumStates;
354 break;
355 }
356 }
357 }
358 rep3 = rep2;
359 rep2 = rep1;
360 rep1 = rep0;
361 rep0 = distance + 1;
362 if (checkDicSize == 0)
363 {
364 if (distance >= processedPos)
365 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
366 }
367 else if (distance >= checkDicSize)
368 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
369 state = (state < kNumStates + kNumLitStates) ? kNumLitStates : kNumLitStates + 3;
370 }
371
372 len += kMatchMinLen;
373
374 if (limit == dicPos)
375 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
376 {
377 SizeT rem = limit - dicPos;
378 unsigned curLen = ((rem < len) ? (unsigned) rem : len);
379 SizeT pos = (dicPos - rep0) + ((dicPos < rep0) ? dicBufSize : 0);
380
381 processedPos += curLen;
382
383 len -= curLen;
384 if (pos + curLen <= dicBufSize)
385 {
386 Byte *dest = dic + dicPos;
387 ptrdiff_t src = (ptrdiff_t) pos - (ptrdiff_t) dicPos;
388 const Byte *lim = dest + curLen;
389 dicPos += curLen;
390 do
391 *(dest) = (Byte) *(dest + src);
392 while (++dest != lim);
393 }
394 else
395 {
396 do
397 {
398 dic[dicPos++] = dic[pos];
399 if (++pos == dicBufSize)
400 pos = 0;
401 } while (--curLen != 0);
402 }
403 }
404 }
405 } while (dicPos < limit && buf < bufLimit);
406 NORMALIZE;
407 p->buf = buf;
408 p->range = range;
409 p->code = code;
410 p->remainLen = len;
411 p->dicPos = dicPos;
412 p->processedPos = processedPos;
413 p->reps[0] = rep0;
414 p->reps[1] = rep1;
415 p->reps[2] = rep2;
416 p->reps[3] = rep3;
417 p->state = state;
418
419 return SZ_OK;
420}
421
422static void MY_FAST_CALL LzmaDec_WriteRem(CLzmaDec *p, SizeT limit)
423{
424 if (p->remainLen != 0 && p->remainLen < kMatchSpecLenStart)
425 {
426 Byte *dic = p->dic;
427 SizeT dicPos = p->dicPos;
428 SizeT dicBufSize = p->dicBufSize;
429 unsigned len = p->remainLen;
430 UInt32 rep0 = p->reps[0];
431 if (limit - dicPos < len)
432 len = (unsigned) (limit - dicPos);
433
434 if (p->checkDicSize == 0 && p->prop.dicSize - p->processedPos <= len)
435 p->checkDicSize = p->prop.dicSize;
436
437 p->processedPos += len;
438 p->remainLen -= len;
439 while (len-- != 0)
440 {
441 dic[dicPos] = dic[(dicPos - rep0) + ((dicPos < rep0) ? dicBufSize : 0)];
442 dicPos++;
443 }
444 p->dicPos = dicPos;
445 }
446}
447
448static int MY_FAST_CALL LzmaDec_DecodeReal2(CLzmaDec *p, SizeT limit, const Byte *bufLimit)
449{
450 do
451 {
452 SizeT limit2 = limit;
453 if (p->checkDicSize == 0)
454 {
455 UInt32 rem = p->prop.dicSize - p->processedPos;
456 if (limit - p->dicPos > rem)
457 limit2 = p->dicPos + rem;
458 }
459 RINOK(LzmaDec_DecodeReal(p, limit2, bufLimit));
460 if (p->processedPos >= p->prop.dicSize)
461 p->checkDicSize = p->prop.dicSize;
462 LzmaDec_WriteRem(p, limit);
463 } while (p->dicPos < limit && p->buf < bufLimit && p->remainLen < kMatchSpecLenStart);
464
465 if (p->remainLen > kMatchSpecLenStart)
466 {
467 p->remainLen = kMatchSpecLenStart;
468 }
469 return 0;
470}
471
472typedef enum
473{
474 DUMMY_ERROR, /* unexpected end of input stream */
475 DUMMY_LIT, DUMMY_MATCH, DUMMY_REP
476} ELzmaDummy;
477
478static ELzmaDummy LzmaDec_TryDummy(const CLzmaDec *p, const Byte *buf, SizeT inSize)
479{
480 UInt32 range = p->range;
481 UInt32 code = p->code;
482 const Byte *bufLimit = buf + inSize;
483 CLzmaProb *probs = p->probs;
484 unsigned state = p->state;
485 ELzmaDummy res;
486
487 {
488 CLzmaProb *prob;
489 UInt32 bound;
490 unsigned ttt;
491 unsigned posState = (p->processedPos) & ((1 << p->prop.pb) - 1);
492
493 prob = probs + IsMatch + (state << kNumPosBitsMax) + posState;
494 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
495 {
496 UPDATE_0_CHECK
497
498 /* if (bufLimit - buf >= 7) return DUMMY_LIT; */
499
500 prob = probs + Literal;
501 if (p->checkDicSize != 0 || p->processedPos != 0)
502 prob += (LZMA_LIT_SIZE * ((((p->processedPos) & ((1 << (p->prop.lp)) - 1)) << p->prop.lc)
503 + (p->dic[(p->dicPos == 0 ? p->dicBufSize : p->dicPos) - 1] >> (8 - p->prop.lc))));
504
505 if (state < kNumLitStates)
506 {
507 unsigned symbol = 1;
508 do
509 {
510 GET_BIT_CHECK(prob + symbol, symbol)
511 } while (symbol < 0x100);
512 }
513 else
514 {
515 unsigned matchByte = p->dic[p->dicPos - p->reps[0] + ((p->dicPos < p->reps[0]) ? p->dicBufSize : 0)];
516 unsigned offs = 0x100;
517 unsigned symbol = 1;
518 do
519 {
520 unsigned bit;
521 CLzmaProb *probLit;
522 matchByte <<= 1;
523 bit = (matchByte & offs);
524 probLit = prob + offs + bit + symbol;
525 GET_BIT2_CHECK(probLit, symbol, offs &= ~bit, offs &= bit)
526 } while (symbol < 0x100);
527 }
528 res = DUMMY_LIT;
529 }
530 else
531 {
532 unsigned len;
533 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
534
535 prob = probs + IsRep + state;
536 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
537 {
538 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
539 state = 0;
540 prob = probs + LenCoder;
541 res = DUMMY_MATCH;
542 }
543 else
544 {
545 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
546 res = DUMMY_REP;
547 prob = probs + IsRepG0 + state;
548 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
549 {
550 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
551 prob = probs + IsRep0Long + (state << kNumPosBitsMax) + posState;
552 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
553 {
554 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
555 NORMALIZE_CHECK;
556 return DUMMY_REP;
557 }
558 else
559 {
560 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
561 }
562 }
563 else
564 {
565 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
566 prob = probs + IsRepG1 + state;
567 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
568 {
569 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
570 }
571 else
572 {
573 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
574 prob = probs + IsRepG2 + state;
575 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(prob)
576 {
577 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
578 }
579 else
580 {
581 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
582 }
583 }
584 }
585 state = kNumStates;
586 prob = probs + RepLenCoder;
587 }
588 {
589 unsigned limit, offset;
590 CLzmaProb *probLen = prob + LenChoice;
591 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(probLen)
592 {
593 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
594 probLen = prob + LenLow + (posState << kLenNumLowBits);
595 offset = 0;
596 limit = 1 << kLenNumLowBits;
597 }
598 else
599 {
600 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
601 probLen = prob + LenChoice2;
602 IF_BIT_0_CHECK(probLen)
603 {
604 UPDATE_0_CHECK;
605 probLen = prob + LenMid + (posState << kLenNumMidBits);
606 offset = kLenNumLowSymbols;
607 limit = 1 << kLenNumMidBits;
608 }
609 else
610 {
611 UPDATE_1_CHECK;
612 probLen = prob + LenHigh;
613 offset = kLenNumLowSymbols + kLenNumMidSymbols;
614 limit = 1 << kLenNumHighBits;
615 }
616 }
617 TREE_DECODE_CHECK(probLen, limit, len);
618 len += offset;
619 }
620
621 if (state < 4)
622 {
623 unsigned posSlot;
624 prob = probs + PosSlot + ((len < kNumLenToPosStates ? len : kNumLenToPosStates - 1) << kNumPosSlotBits);
625 TREE_DECODE_CHECK(prob, 1 << kNumPosSlotBits, posSlot);
626 if (posSlot >= kStartPosModelIndex)
627 {
628 int numDirectBits = ((posSlot >> 1) - 1);
629
630 /* if (bufLimit - buf >= 8) return DUMMY_MATCH; */
631
632 if (posSlot < kEndPosModelIndex)
633 {
634 prob = probs + SpecPos + ((2 | (posSlot & 1)) << numDirectBits) - posSlot - 1;
635 }
636 else
637 {
638 numDirectBits -= kNumAlignBits;
639 do
640 {
641 NORMALIZE_CHECK
642 range >>= 1;
643 code -= range & (((code - range) >> 31) - 1);
644 /* if (code >= range) code -= range; */
645 } while (--numDirectBits != 0);
646 prob = probs + Align;
647 numDirectBits = kNumAlignBits;
648 }
649 {
650 unsigned i = 1;
651 do
652 {
653 GET_BIT_CHECK(prob + i, i);
654 } while (--numDirectBits != 0);
655 }
656 }
657 }
658 }
659 }
660 NORMALIZE_CHECK;
661 return res;
662}
663
664static void LzmaDec_InitRc(CLzmaDec *p, const Byte *data)
665{
666 p->code = ((UInt32) data[1] << 24) | ((UInt32) data[2] << 16) | ((UInt32) data[3] << 8) | ((UInt32) data[4]);
667 p->range = 0xFFFFFFFF;
668 p->needFlush = 0;
669}
670
671void LzmaDec_InitDicAndState(CLzmaDec *p, Bool initDic, Bool initState)
672{
673 p->needFlush = 1;
674 p->remainLen = 0;
675 p->tempBufSize = 0;
676
677 if (initDic)
678 {
679 p->processedPos = 0;
680 p->checkDicSize = 0;
681 p->needInitState = 1;
682 }
683 if (initState)
684 p->needInitState = 1;
685}
686
687void LzmaDec_Init(CLzmaDec *p)
688{
689 p->dicPos = 0;
690 LzmaDec_InitDicAndState(p, True, True);
691}
692
693static void LzmaDec_InitStateReal(CLzmaDec *p)
694{
695 UInt32 numProbs = Literal + ((UInt32) LZMA_LIT_SIZE << (p->prop.lc + p->prop.lp));
696 UInt32 i;
697 CLzmaProb *probs = p->probs;
698 for (i = 0; i < numProbs; i++)
699 probs[i] = kBitModelTotal >> 1;
700 p->reps[0] = p->reps[1] = p->reps[2] = p->reps[3] = 1;
701 p->state = 0;
702 p->needInitState = 0;
703}
704
705SRes LzmaDec_DecodeToDic(CLzmaDec *p, SizeT dicLimit, const Byte *src, SizeT *srcLen, ELzmaFinishMode finishMode, ELzmaStatus *status)
706{
707 SizeT inSize = *srcLen;
708 (*srcLen) = 0;
709 LzmaDec_WriteRem(p, dicLimit);
710
711 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NOT_SPECIFIED;
712
713 while (p->remainLen != kMatchSpecLenStart)
714 {
715 int checkEndMarkNow;
716
717 if (p->needFlush != 0)
718 {
719 for (; inSize > 0 && p->tempBufSize < RC_INIT_SIZE; (*srcLen)++, inSize--)
720 p->tempBuf[p->tempBufSize++] = *src++;
721 if (p->tempBufSize < RC_INIT_SIZE)
722 {
723 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT;
724 return SZ_OK;
725 }
726 if (p->tempBuf[0] != 0)
727 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
728
729 LzmaDec_InitRc(p, p->tempBuf);
730 p->tempBufSize = 0;
731 }
732
733 checkEndMarkNow = 0;
734 if (p->dicPos >= dicLimit)
735 {
736 if (p->remainLen == 0 && p->code == 0)
737 {
738 *status = LZMA_STATUS_MAYBE_FINISHED_WITHOUT_MARK;
739 return SZ_OK;
740 }
741 if (finishMode == LZMA_FINISH_ANY)
742 {
743 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NOT_FINISHED;
744 return SZ_OK;
745 }
746 if (p->remainLen != 0)
747 {
748 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NOT_FINISHED;
749 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
750 }
751 checkEndMarkNow = 1;
752 }
753
754 if (p->needInitState)
755 LzmaDec_InitStateReal(p);
756
757 if (p->tempBufSize == 0)
758 {
759 SizeT processed;
760 const Byte *bufLimit;
761 if (inSize < LZMA_REQUIRED_INPUT_MAX || checkEndMarkNow)
762 {
763 int dummyRes = LzmaDec_TryDummy(p, src, inSize);
764 if (dummyRes == DUMMY_ERROR)
765 {
766 memcpy(p->tempBuf, src, inSize);
767 p->tempBufSize = (unsigned) inSize;
768 (*srcLen) += inSize;
769 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT;
770 return SZ_OK;
771 }
772 if (checkEndMarkNow && dummyRes != DUMMY_MATCH)
773 {
774 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NOT_FINISHED;
775 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
776 }
777 bufLimit = src;
778 }
779 else
780 bufLimit = src + inSize - LZMA_REQUIRED_INPUT_MAX;
781 p->buf = src;
782 if (LzmaDec_DecodeReal2(p, dicLimit, bufLimit) != 0)
783 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
784 processed = (SizeT) (p->buf - src);
785 (*srcLen) += processed;
786 src += processed;
787 inSize -= processed;
788 }
789 else
790 {
791 unsigned rem = p->tempBufSize, lookAhead = 0;
792 while (rem < LZMA_REQUIRED_INPUT_MAX && lookAhead < inSize)
793 p->tempBuf[rem++] = src[lookAhead++];
794 p->tempBufSize = rem;
795 if (rem < LZMA_REQUIRED_INPUT_MAX || checkEndMarkNow)
796 {
797 int dummyRes = LzmaDec_TryDummy(p, p->tempBuf, rem);
798 if (dummyRes == DUMMY_ERROR)
799 {
800 (*srcLen) += lookAhead;
801 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT;
802 return SZ_OK;
803 }
804 if (checkEndMarkNow && dummyRes != DUMMY_MATCH)
805 {
806 *status = LZMA_STATUS_NOT_FINISHED;
807 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
808 }
809 }
810 p->buf = p->tempBuf;
811 if (LzmaDec_DecodeReal2(p, dicLimit, p->buf) != 0)
812 return SZ_ERROR_DATA;
813 lookAhead -= (rem - (unsigned) (p->buf - p->tempBuf));
814 (*srcLen) += lookAhead;
815 src += lookAhead;
816 inSize -= lookAhead;
817 p->tempBufSize = 0;
818 }
819 }
820 if (p->code == 0)
821 *status = LZMA_STATUS_FINISHED_WITH_MARK;
822 return (p->code == 0) ? SZ_OK : SZ_ERROR_DATA;
823}
824
825SRes LzmaDec_DecodeToBuf(CLzmaDec *p, Byte *dest, SizeT *destLen, const Byte *src, SizeT *srcLen, ELzmaFinishMode finishMode,
826 ELzmaStatus *status)
827{
828 SizeT outSize = *destLen;
829 SizeT inSize = *srcLen;
830 *srcLen = *destLen = 0;
831 for (;;)
832 {
833 SizeT inSizeCur = inSize, outSizeCur, dicPos;
834 ELzmaFinishMode curFinishMode;
835 SRes res;
836 if (p->dicPos == p->dicBufSize)
837 p->dicPos = 0;
838 dicPos = p->dicPos;
839 if (outSize > p->dicBufSize - dicPos)
840 {
841 outSizeCur = p->dicBufSize;
842 curFinishMode = LZMA_FINISH_ANY;
843 }
844 else
845 {
846 outSizeCur = dicPos + outSize;
847 curFinishMode = finishMode;
848 }
849
850 res = LzmaDec_DecodeToDic(p, outSizeCur, src, &inSizeCur, curFinishMode, status);
851 src += inSizeCur;
852 inSize -= inSizeCur;
853 *srcLen += inSizeCur;
854 outSizeCur = p->dicPos - dicPos;
855 memcpy(dest, p->dic + dicPos, outSizeCur);
856 dest += outSizeCur;
857 outSize -= outSizeCur;
858 *destLen += outSizeCur;
859 if (res != 0)
860 return res;
861 if (outSizeCur == 0 || outSize == 0)
862 return SZ_OK;
863 }
864}

866void LzmaDec_FreeProbs(CLzmaDec *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
867{
868 alloc->Free(alloc, p->probs);
869 p->probs = 0;
870}

872static void LzmaDec_FreeDict(CLzmaDec *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
873{
874 alloc->Free(alloc, p->dic);
875 p->dic = 0;
876}

878void LzmaDec_Free(CLzmaDec *p, ISzAlloc *alloc)
879{
880 LzmaDec_FreeProbs(p, alloc);
881 LzmaDec_FreeDict(p, alloc);
882}

884SRes LzmaProps_Decode(CLzmaProps *p, const Byte *data, unsigned size)
885{
886 UInt32 dicSize;
887 Byte d;
888
889 if (size < LZMA_PROPS_SIZE)
890 return SZ_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED;
891 else
892 dicSize = data[1] | ((UInt32) data[2] << 8) | ((UInt32) data[3] << 16) | ((UInt32) data[4] << 24);
893
894 if (dicSize < LZMA_DIC_MIN)
895 dicSize = LZMA_DIC_MIN;
896 p->dicSize = dicSize;
897
898 d = data[0];
899 if (d >= (9 * 5 * 5))
900 return SZ_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED;
901
902 p->lc = d % 9;
903 d /= 9;
904 p->pb = d / 5;
905 p->lp = d % 5;
906
907 return SZ_OK;
908}
909
910static SRes LzmaDec_AllocateProbs2(CLzmaDec *p, const CLzmaProps *propNew, ISzAlloc *alloc)
911{
912 UInt32 numProbs = LzmaProps_GetNumProbs(propNew);
913 if (p->probs == 0 || numProbs != p->numProbs)
914 {
915 LzmaDec_FreeProbs(p, alloc);
916 p->probs = (CLzmaProb *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, numProbs * sizeof(CLzmaProb));
917 p->numProbs = numProbs;
918 if (p->probs == 0)
919 return SZ_ERROR_MEM;
920 }
921 return SZ_OK;
922}
923
924SRes LzmaDec_AllocateProbs(CLzmaDec *p, const Byte *props, unsigned propsSize, ISzAlloc *alloc)
925{
926 CLzmaProps propNew;
927 RINOK(LzmaProps_Decode(&propNew, props, propsSize));
928 RINOK(LzmaDec_AllocateProbs2(p, &propNew, alloc));
929 p->prop = propNew;
930 return SZ_OK;
931}
932
933SRes LzmaDec_Allocate(CLzmaDec *p, const Byte *props, unsigned propsSize, ISzAlloc *alloc)
934{
935 CLzmaProps propNew;
936 SizeT dicBufSize;
937 RINOK(LzmaProps_Decode(&propNew, props, propsSize));
938 RINOK(LzmaDec_AllocateProbs2(p, &propNew, alloc));
939 dicBufSize = propNew.dicSize;
940 if (p->dic == 0 || dicBufSize != p->dicBufSize)
941 {
942 LzmaDec_FreeDict(p, alloc);
943 p->dic = (Byte *) alloc->Alloc(alloc, dicBufSize);
944 if (p->dic == 0)
945 {
946 LzmaDec_FreeProbs(p, alloc);
947 return SZ_ERROR_MEM;
948 }
949 }
950 p->dicBufSize = dicBufSize;
951 p->prop = propNew;
952 return SZ_OK;
953}
954
955SRes LzmaDecode(Byte *dest, SizeT *destLen, const Byte *src, SizeT *srcLen, const Byte *propData, unsigned propSize,
956 ELzmaFinishMode finishMode, ELzmaStatus *status, ISzAlloc *alloc)
957{
958 CLzmaDec p;
959 SRes res;
960 SizeT inSize = *srcLen;
961 SizeT outSize = *destLen;
962 *srcLen = *destLen = 0;
963 if (inSize < RC_INIT_SIZE)
964 return SZ_ERROR_INPUT_EOF;
965
966 LzmaDec_Construct(&p);
967 res = LzmaDec_AllocateProbs(&p, propData, propSize, alloc);
968 if (res != 0)
969 return res;
970 p.dic = dest;
971 p.dicBufSize = outSize;
972
973 LzmaDec_Init(&p);
974
975 *srcLen = inSize;
976 res = LzmaDec_DecodeToDic(&p, outSize, src, srcLen, finishMode, status);
977
978 if (res == SZ_OK && *status == LZMA_STATUS_NEEDS_MORE_INPUT)
979 res = SZ_ERROR_INPUT_EOF;
980
981 (*destLen) = p.dicPos;
982 LzmaDec_FreeProbs(&p, alloc);
983 return res;
984}
